The algorithms used to score splice site PSSMs have been previously published19. In summary, to score the splice sites, it is necessary to obtain the genome’s PSSMs of the 3′ and 5′ splice sites incorporating all human exons. The 3’ss was defined as the 20 intronic nucleotides upstream of exons and the first three exonic nucleotides, whereas the 5’ss was defined as the three terminal exonic nucleotides and the first six intronic nucleotides of the downstream intron. Only G[T/C]-AG exons were used for this analysis. Subsequently, every splice site was scored based on its adherence to the human PSSM, as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
